column1: I feel kind of like trash. Today's been bad and my expectations haven't been met in a variety of ways. I feel angered and honestly somewhat disrespected, and mostly in the mood to just relax and vent my emotions.

I am feeling anxious but also excited. There is a lot of uncertainty in the world right now, with the coronavirus and the Trump presidency/election news. It's hard to feel settled. But we're also doing fun and great things that are wonderful-- watching Kelly discover new skills and plan the next steps in her life, changing (drastically) the look of the home we've lived in for 17 years and planning exciting trips.

I have no confidence in technology. I want to quit my job because of politics. My family thinks I am lazy at computers. I am tired of being disappointed in the country. I have no idea what I will do in retirement. I am uncertain of the future and it makes me anxious.

column1:
I'm doing pretty good- I just switched teams at work, from pricing to dispatch. I'll get to learn a lot of new things on the new team, like Go and various related concurrency programming, but I'll definitely miss my old team. I'm also really excited- my girlfriend is moving to SF next week!

In a big sense, the most important thing going on right now is coronavirus. Coronavirus is a virus that originated in Wuhan, but has since become a global pandemic! The root cause, you ask? Those weirdos are eating some wack meats! I'll stick to tofu, thank you very much.

I’m doing overall well! Feeling happy with where my life is currently at, although feel impending stress about deciding what my next step will be. I’m satisfied with my work, health, and personal projects as well. As to what’s going on, I’m nearing the end of my service in peace corps and currently have family visiting me.
